post_text:
Tonight we start selling our discount cards, previously known as Gold Cards. This year to limit face to face contact we will be offering a mobile app called RAH RAH that works the similarly to a Gold Card but it is an App on your phone. This app works anywhere in the United States. Which means whether you go on vacation or stay local the the discounts work. If interested please contact a high school athlete or coach and we can get you on board. This is a fundraiser for our Booster Club.

High School athletes make sure to attend the RAHRAH informational/kickoff meeting tonight. The zoom link is under Activities > Athletic Forms on the school website.

Post contains School Board Meeting Info and Links

Parents,
The next School Board Meeting is Monday 7/13/20 at 6pm in the Elementary Commons. The Back to School Plan (BSP) is on the agenda. The BSP link is attached and is currently a work in progress as information and guidelines from various departments needs to be addressed, but is changing daily. Again, the BSP is a work in progress.

The BSP includes 3 phases - Full Open (Green Phase), Hybrid (Yellow Phase), Distance Learning (Red Phase). Distance Learning will be a full time option available to families, but once a family has chosen this option, it will remain that way for the entire Semester.

Please see links for more info on the meeting.

Meeting Agenda

https://www.flandreau.k12.sd.us/cms/lib/SD02206229/Centricity/domain/89/2020-2021%20board/2020%20July%20Packet.pdf

Back To School Plan

post_text: Graduation is tomorrow (May 16th) at 2pm. Cards/Gifts for grads may be dropped off at the school between 8a-noon, or following the ceremony to 4p. Reserved parking is for graduates and their immediate families. Guests attending may only park in spaces that are not reserved. Guests are not to get out of their vehicles. There will be no facilities available, so please attend to personal needs before arriving. The graduation ceremony will be livestreamed at flandreau.k12.sd.us, where you can also find the parade route. Congratulations, Class of 2020!

Educational Testing Consultants Inc. (ETC) is offering free programming for all programs (pre-college and graduate). These programs will be online sessions touching on topics like the following:

• Intro to the GRE
• GRE Math Strategies
• GRE Verbal Strategies
• Essay Writing for Grad Testing
• Intro to the ACT and SAT
• Pre-College Math Strategies
• Pre-College Verbal Strategies

Update on next week’s school closure and our distance learning plan.

Distance Learning packets for all grade levels will be linked on the school’s website as well as available for pick-up in the Elementary Commons on Monday from 9:00 am to 3:00 pm. Teachers will be contacting parents and students starting on Monday with more details.

As per CDC recommendations on mass gatherings, all school activities will be POSTPONED until further notice. This includes Prom, All-School Play, Athletic practices, etc.

Grab and Go lunches will be provided on weekdays through the closure from 11:00 am to 1:00 pm in front of the high school. The sack lunches will now include a breakfast for the following day.

If you need to get school supplies from your locker, etc., please go to the school’s front doors of the elementary, middle school or high school between 9:00 am and 3:00 pm on Monday. A staff member will assist you.

Thank you for your patience and understanding in this unprecedented time.

post_text: Effective right now - we can offer food for all children 0-18, regardless of if they are enrolled at FPS. Please come grab a sack lunch from 11am to 1pm today and tomorrow!
shared_text:
Flandreau Public School
March 14 at 1:36 PM ·

Student Lunch

The Flandreau School District will be offering free lunches to all our students during the unexpected closure on March 16-18. March 19-20 were already scheduled days off on the master school calendar, so meals will not be offered on those dates. Meals can be picked up from 11:00 am to 1:00 pm on Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday at the high school entrance. These meals will be pre-packaged and handed to you drive-up style, please just pull up/walk up to the curb and someone will assist you. We do need each student’s name as meals are picked up for tracking in our system, but you will not be charged for the meal regardless of your meal status (free, reduced, or full-pay). Students may not stay onsite to eat, we must distribute the meals to be eaten elsewhere. We encourage all students to take advantage of this program.

The Flandreau School District will be offering free lunches to all our students during the unexpected closure on March 16-18. March 19-20 were already scheduled days off on the master school calendar, so meals will not be offered on those dates. Meals can be picked up from 11:00 am to 1:00 pm on Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday at the high school entrance. These meals will be pre-packaged and handed to you drive-up style, please just pull up/walk up to the curb and someone will assist you. We do need each student’s name as meals are picked up for tracking in our system, but you will not be charged for the meal regardless of your meal status (free, reduced, or full-pay). Students may not stay onsite to eat, we must distribute the meals to be eaten elsewhere. We encourage all students to take advantage of this program.

post_text: Senior Jordyn Hall was recently named a recipient of the Horatio Alger Scholarship! As one of the nation's largest need-based college scholarship programs in the country, the Horatio Alger Scholarship Programs specifically assist high school students who have faced and overcome great obstacles in their young lives. This scholarship is $10,000 per year for four years, worth $40,000! Congrats Jordyn!

"The music boosters board has made a decision to cancel tomorrow evenings carnival due to the continued poor weather we are forecast to have overnight this evening and through tomorrow. Please continue to have your student sell raffle tickets. The raffle will be held at the High School concert on May 2.

Also, the Junior High Instrumental contest, scheduled for Saturday in Flandreau, will be postponed. More information will be given to JH students at a later date.

Thank you for your patience and understanding. Please let us know if you have any questions.

Flandreau Music Boosters"

Thank you for your patience and understanding. Please let us know if you have any questions.

Flandreau Music Boosters"
